\fs36 Application Icons\

\fs16 \
\

\b0\fs28\li2100 Freestanding and docked icons are the same size as miniwindows and have the same beveled border to make them look raised above the screen.  Each icon window displays the icon for an application–an image that on the MegaPixel Display can be no more than 48 pixels high by 48 pixels wide, so that it can fit comfortably in the 64 pixel by 64 pixel window.\

\fs16 \
\

\fs28 The docked icon for an application that isn't running displays the same image that represents the application in a directory window.  However, you can provide an icon for the application when it's running that's different from, but related to, the icon found in a directory window.\

